Payment Terms:
MESCOM will errange payment of 100% value of materiais plus Taxes and Duties on receipt of goods in good condition
after inspection and verification of materials at the destination and against presentation of dispatch and other documents as
specified below by means of cheque after satisfying the terms and conditions of the order and receipt of Material
Acknowledgement Statement from the Consignes Stores. For arranging 100% payment, the following documents will have
to be furnished by the supplier.
1
2
Bank Guarantee may be extended for any further period,if so required by MESCOM.
In case vandor fails to furnish the required Security Deposit in the prescribed format then 5.0% of the value of the
supplier bill shall be deducted as security deposit at the time of payment.
Security Deposit is refundable. Bank Guarantee can be released.
6
(a) After satisfactory completion of the supply and after the payment of final bill.
(b) After the expay of the period of warranty/Guarantee.
Delivery Challan duly acknowledged by Consignee. The payment will be arranged against clear acknowledgment
duly signed by the Storekeeper and Store Officer of the relevant MESCOM Stores
3 Material Acknowledgment Statement (to be fumished by Consignes)
4
Approved Test Certificate or reference letter of COMPANY approving the last certificate
5
The arrangement for payment of "Tax Amount" will be made only after the Invoice details of the respective month are
uploaded in GSTR-1 by the Supplier
The triplicate and quadruplicato copies of the invoicos may
Material Acknowledgement Statement
Guarantee Certificate
7
Tax Invoice comprising of GSTIN of the Supplier & MESCOM (29AADCM7029H1ZA) duly indicating the IGST, SGST
& CGST separately in duplicate, stamped and pre-receipted
pent to the foagective consignoes for submission of
may boong!
Penalty For Late Delivery:
In case the materials are not delivered within the stipulated delivery schedule, you shall be flable to pay at the
discretion of the Purchase Committee or the company as the case may be, Penalty at 0.5% per Week or part thereof,
subject to a maximum of 10.0% of the order value, of such complete portion or section of the plant, equipment or
materials including the portion supplied, which could not be brought into commission due to any part thereof not
having been delivered in time, subject to force majeure condition. Otherwise it should be specifically as noted in the
schedule.
ved
Suit For Proceedings:
Any sult or proceedings arising out of this contract shall be instituted in law courts at Mangaluru.
Guarantee
The material offered shall be guaranteed for satisfactory operation and against failure due to bad workmanship and
inherent defects in design or materials for a period of 18 months from the date of supply or 12 months from the date of
commissioning whichever is earlier. The supplier shall make good by replacing with new material within 30 days from
the date of intimation, at his own cost that fall during the guarantee period.
Purchase Order No: [28183]2018-19/760 /344
Packing
a) The SUPPLIER shall provide such packing of the goods as required to prevent their damage or deterioration
during transit to final destination as well as storage till its layout and testing as indicated in the contract. The packing
shall be sufficient to withstand, without limitations, rough handling during transit by road, and/or rail and exposure of
rain, humidity, extreme temperatures, salt and precipitation during transit and open storage for long durations.
Packing case size and weights shall be determined taking into consideration where appropriate, the remoteness of
the goods final destination and the transit and the availability of handling facility at all points, availability of the various
trucks/trallers for transportation. The PURCHASER shall not entertain any claim whatsoever, in this regard.
